Job Description
Job ID: HNMJD1480
Job Title: Data Integration specialist

Location: Leeuwarden, Netherlands
Language: Dutch

Description:
The ideal candidate has on the one hand a passion for technology, in-depth and extensive experience with (data) links between various IT environments and on the other hand is able to provide service in a customer-oriented and committed manner. You advise colleagues and external parties about the design of software systems and links and related technical choices.
As a Data integration specialist you are responsible for:
Implementing the data integration platform and storage needs;
The management of setting up and maintaining data links in common protocols such as SOAP and REST as well as sector-specific or older standards;
Design, develop, automate and support data flow models for extracting, transforming and loading data;
Creating and improving data exchange.
You are also responsible for collecting, processing and analyzing data and you translate functional requirements into designs for data access, transformation, movement requirements and availability. You take responsibility from start to finish within this functional area.

Job requirements:-
HBO or WO work and thinking level;
At least 3 years of relevant work experience in a similar position;
Demonstrated knowledge of ETL processes, Microsoft SQL, Progress OpenEdge RDBMS;
Experience with data modeling techniques;
Experience with data management and information management;
Knowledge of data warehousing concepts and tooling;
Data quality frameworks;
Experience with business intelligence processes;
In addition, you are analytical and you can build bridges. You also have good communication skills in speech and writing.
Preferred knowledge of 1 or more of the following subjects:
Azure Data lake
Knowledge of API and Event techniques;
Knowledge of data science such as business analytics and artificial analytics (AI);
Familiar with Agile / Scrum working.
